{"id":"2208.12339","submitter":"Zhiwei Fan","authors":"Zhiwei Fan, Paraschos Koutris, Xiating Ouyang, Jef Wijsen","title":"LinCQA: Faster Consistent Query Answering with Linear Time Guarantees","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"cs.DB","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Most data analytical pipelines often encounter the problem of querying\ninconsistent data that violate pre-determined integrity constraints. Data\ncleaning is an extensively studied paradigm that singles out a consistent\nrepair of the inconsistent data. Consistent query answering (CQA) is an\nalternative approach to data cleaning that asks for all tuples guaranteed to be\nreturned by a given query on all (in most cases, exponentially many) repairs of\nthe inconsistent data. This paper identifies a class of acyclic\nselect-project-join (SPJ) queries for which CQA can be solved via SQL rewriting\nwith a linear time guarantee. Our rewriting method can be viewed as a\ngeneralization of Yannakakis's algorithm for acyclic joins to the inconsistent\nsetting. We present LinCQA, a system that can output rewritings in both SQL and\nnon-recursive Datalog rules for every query in this class. We show that LinCQA\noften outperforms the existing CQA systems on both synthetic and real-world\nworkloads, and in some cases, by orders of magnitude.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 25 Aug 2022 20:43:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-29"}
